## Optimization Summary: Q17 Iteration 1

### Bottleneck Identified
**Phase 1 (Precompute Thresholds)** consumed **99.9% of total execution time** (103,052 ms out of 103,113 ms):
- Root cause: **Critical section contention** in the parallel loop with `#pragma omp critical`
- All 60M lineitem rows competed to update a single global hash table via critical section
- With 64 CPU cores, this caused massive lock contention and serialization

### Optimization Applied
**Thread-Local Aggregation Pattern** (Partial Aggregation):

1. **Before**: Global hash table with critical section
   ```cpp
   #pragma omp parallel for
   for (...) {
       #pragma omp critical
       { partkey_stats[pk] += qty; }  // All threads serialize here
   }
   ```

2. **After**: Thread-local hash tables, merge after loop
   ```cpp
   vector<unordered_map<...>> thread_local_stats(num_threads);
   
   #pragma omp parallel for
   for (...) {
       int tid = omp_get_thread_num();
       thread_local_stats[tid][pk] += qty;  // No lock contention
   }
   
   // Merge all thread-local maps into final result
   for (int t = 0; t < num_threads; t++)
       for (auto& [pk, stats] : thread_local_stats[t])
           partkey_stats[pk] += stats;
   ```

### Performance Improvement
| Metric | Before | After | Speedup |
|--------|--------|-------|---------|
| Phase 1 | 103,052.57 ms | 23,529.20 ms | **4.38x** |
| Total Time | 103,113.18 ms | 23,605.18 ms | **4.36x** |

